{
  "text": "Usually FAs are asymptomatic but, in up to 20% of cases [CITATION_1] they can be multiple and bilateral, increasing the possibility of clinical detection at palpation. FAs are generally no larger than 2-3 cm, except the juvenile giant subtypes. Gordon et al [CITATION_2] reported a safe growth rate of 20% in all three dimensions over a period of 6 months, for all age groups.",
